<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[264,1325,719,1745]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[432,565,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankusha">
<emphasis box="[432,565,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. ankusha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[925,1047,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[925,1047,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having entire, conically produced pygophore and spatulate, medially twisted aedeagal shaft. It is not closely related to any of the included species in the genus though it shares the characters of the male pygophore with 
<taxonomicName box="[520,677,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressa">
<emphasis box="[520,677,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">X. compressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
